<h1 id="setup-vendor-master-and-purchase-order-to-be-target-of-consolidated-invoice" sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="28">Setup vendor master and purchase order to be target of consolidated invoice</h1>


<p sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="32">In Japan, the vendors usually use consolidated invoice for transactions.</p>
<p sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="36">This task walks you through configuring a vendor master and purchase order to use the consolidated invoice.</p>
<p sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="40">This task was created using the demo data company JPMF.</p>
<h2 id="set-up-vendor-master" sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="43">Set up vendor master</h2>
<ol sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="44">
<li sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="44">Go to Accounts payable &gt; Vendors &gt; All vendors.</li>
<li sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="45">In the list, click the link in the selected row.</li>
<li sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="46">Expand or collapse the Payment section.
<ul sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="47">
<li sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="47">Verify that the terms of payment uses the Cutoff day.</li>
<li sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="48">Specify a Consolidation day for the vendor.</li>
<li sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="49">You might need to click Edit first, before you can update this field.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="set-a-purchase-order-to-be-target-of-consolidated-invoice" sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="51">Set a purchase order to be target of consolidated invoice</h2>
<ol sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="52">
<li sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="52">Go to Accounts payable &gt; Purchase orders &gt; All purchase orders.</li>
<li sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="53">In the list, click the link in the selected row.</li>
<li sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="54">On the Action Pane, click Options.</li>
<li sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="55">Click Change view.</li>
<li sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="56">Click Header view.
<ul sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="57">
<li sourcefile="articles/finance/localizations/tasks/vendor-master-po.md" sourcestartlinenumber="57">Verify that the Target of consolidation slider is set to 'Yes'.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
</article>
